68. l. Agrigentinum. Empedocles a philoso- pher, poet, and historian of Agrigentum in Sicily. , According to Horace, this enthusiast, wishing to be thought a god, threw himself into the crater of AEtna and perished there.

6810. Tota carrad. “Through the theatre.” The theatra was of an oblong semicircular form, like the half of an amphitheatra. The benches or aeats rose above one another, and were distributed to the different orders in the sarna manner as in tha amphitheatra The foremost rows next the stage, called orchestra, were assigned to the senators and ambassadors of foreign states: fourteen rows be· hind them to the Equites and the rest to the people. The whole was called Cocco.
